From: Antonio de Angelis <Antonio.deAngelis@arm.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Aug 2022 13:06:07 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 6/7] Initialise driver wrappers as first step in
 psa_crypto_init()

This patch amends the order of initialisations performed in psa_crypto_init()
to make sure that the driver wrappers based on the PSA driver API are initialised
just after the key slots in memory, both of them at the beginning of the
initialisation sequence.

Signed-off-by: Antonio de Angelis <antonio.deangelis@arm.com>
---
 library/psa_crypto.c | 16 ++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/library/psa_crypto.c b/library/psa_crypto.c
index 43c8b9e6a..d8a393343 100644
--- a/library/psa_crypto.c
+++ b/library/psa_crypto.c
@@ -6327,14 +6327,6 @@ psa_status_t psa_crypto_init( void )
     if( global_data.initialized != 0 )
         return( PSA_SUCCESS );
 
-    /* Initialize and seed the random generator. */
-    mbedtls_psa_random_init( &global_data.rng );
-    global_data.rng_state = RNG_INITIALIZED;
-    status = mbedtls_psa_random_seed( &global_data.rng );
-    if( status != PSA_SUCCESS )
-        goto exit;
-    global_data.rng_state = RNG_SEEDED;
-
     status = psa_initialize_key_slots( );
     if( status != PSA_SUCCESS )
         goto exit;
@@ -6344,6 +6336,14 @@ psa_status_t psa_crypto_init( void )
     if( status != PSA_SUCCESS )
         goto exit;
 
+    /* Initialize and seed the random generator. */
+    mbedtls_psa_random_init( &global_data.rng );
+    global_data.rng_state = RNG_INITIALIZED;
+    status = mbedtls_psa_random_seed( &global_data.rng );
+    if( status != PSA_SUCCESS )
+        goto exit;
+    global_data.rng_state = RNG_SEEDED;
+
 #if defined(PSA_CRYPTO_STORAGE_HAS_TRANSACTIONS)
     status = psa_crypto_load_transaction( );
     if( status == PSA_SUCCESS )
